                            <comment id="17738057" author="adelapena" created="Wed, 28 Jun 2023 11:15:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The proposed patch follows the approach that was discussed for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18617&quot; title=&quot;Disable the deprecated keyspace/table thresholds and convert them to Guardrails&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-18617&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-18617&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The deprecated properties are removed from &lt;tt&gt;cassandra.yaml&lt;/tt&gt; and transformed into the equivalent guardrails with a &lt;tt&gt;@Replaces&lt;/tt&gt; tag. If an old &lt;tt&gt;cassandra.yaml&lt;/tt&gt; contains the old properties they will be used to set the guardrails. But if they are absent, they will be disabled by default, same as the guardrail.&lt;/p&gt;
